docs.title: Smith of Wootton Major
first_sentence:
here was a village once, not very long ago for
those with long memories, nor
very far away for those with long legs.
Wootton Major it was called because it was larger than
Wootton Minor, a few miles away-deep in the trees;
but it was not very large, though it was at that time
prosperous, and a fair number of folk lived in it, good,
bad, and mixed, as is usual.
